name: 李老师不是你老师
content:
Netizen contribution
Today, a topic [#Chinese students say they can't sympathize with the atomic bomb in Hiroshima#, Japanese MP: Unacceptable, will investigate to the end] topped the trending searches on Weibo
In the video, two Chinese students in Japan talked about the atomic bomb in Hiroshima during a food review video in Hiroshima, Japan, and their remarks sparked controversy in Japan.
At the same time, because the two claimed to have received the "Peace Culture" scholarship in Hiroshima, Japanese netizens called for the cancellation of the two's scholarships and degree certificates. A local MP in Hiroshima posted a message saying "Unacceptable, will investigate to the end".

name: 李老师不是你老师
content: The topic quickly topped the hot search list and attracted a lot of attention from netizens. In the comment section, a large number of netizens expressed their support for the two international students. In response, Hu Xijin also reposted it and said that the two students were just expressing their true feelings and had no intention of deliberately provoking Japanese society. It would be too low if the local government of Hiroshima sanctioned the two Chinese international students for this.
